msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/date"
msgid "16th January 1942 - Glushkovo"
msgstr "16 de enero de 1942 - Glushkovo"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/doctrine_allround"
msgid "Doctrine: All-Round"
msgstr "Doctrina: completa"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/doctrine_defensive"
msgid "Doctrine: Defensive"
msgstr "Doctrina: defensiva"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/doctrine_irregular"
msgid "Doctrine: Irregular"
msgstr "Doctrina: irregular"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/doctrine_offensive"
msgid "Doctrine: Offensive"
msgstr "Doctrina: ofensiva"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/lose_troops"
msgid "You lost all your men!"
msgstr "¡Has perdido a todos tus hombres!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/mission_option_select1"
msgid "SELECT YOUR TACTICAL DOCTRINE:"
msgstr "SELECCIONA UNA DOCTRINA TÁCTICA:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/name"
msgid "Back to Square One"
msgstr "Vuelta al punto de partida"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/name_big"
msgid "Back to Square One"
msgstr "Vuelta al punto de partida"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/leutnant/01"
msgid ""
"God allmighty, this place looked much better the first time we came around."
msgstr "Santo Dios, este sitio tenía mucho mejor aspecto la primera vez que vinimos."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/leutnant/02"
msgid ""
"Shut it. Our situation is no laughing matter. We're about to be surrounded "
"by an overwhelming force with little to counter their relentless "
"counterattack. The only thing playing in our favour is the stellar "
"performance of our close air support."
msgstr "Cierra la boca. No estamos para reírnos. Múltiples tropas nos rodean y no podemos hacer casi nada para evitarlo. Nuestra última esperanza es el apoyo aéreo, dependemos de que hagan una actuación estelar."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/leutnant/03"
msgid "The Mayo"
msgstr "The Mayo"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/leutnant/04"
msgid "Herr Hauptmann, reporting in as requested!"
msgstr "¡Al habla Herr Hauptmann!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/01"
msgid ""
"Good to have you here! Come closer. You once lead the assault on this "
"sector, today I need you to defend it with the help of our air force."
msgstr "¡Qué alegría tenerte! Acércate. Sé que una vez dirigiste un asalto en este sector, pero hoy necesito que lo protejas con ayuda de nuestras tropas aéreas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/02"
msgid ""
"I expect a full soviet assault on the north and north-west. We are the only "
"thing standing in the way of the Soviets and the encirclement of our armies. "
"There will be no more retreats, am I making myself clear?"
msgstr "Creemos que los soviéticos atacarán el norte y noroeste con todo. De camino al embolsamiento de nuestros ejércitos solo nos interponemos nosotros. No se permiten más retiradas, ¿queda claro?"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/03"
msgid ""
"I am assigning you a brigade of our most devastating weapon against the "
"bolshevik armor - the 8,8cm Anti-aircraft guns. You should plan your tactics "
"entirely around these guns."
msgstr "Te voy a asignar una brigada de nuestra arma más devastadora frente al blindaje bolchevique: el cañón antiaéreo de 8,8 cm. Elabora tu estrategia en base a los cañones."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/04"
msgid ""
"These men are our artillery signallers. Their flares will mark the way for "
"Hoepner's 4th army artillery. Use them sparingly. The Luftwaffe squadron "
"ZG26 will support your ground forces. Good luck, Herr Leutnant!"
msgstr "Estos hombres son controladores de artillería. Las bengalas que portan marcan el camino de la 4.ª artillería de Hopener. Úsalas con moderación. El escuadrón de la Luftwaffe ZG26 apoyará a tus tropas terrestres. ¡Buena suerte, Herr Leutnant!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/05"
msgid "Find some cover! The enemy is about to start a fireworks display!"
msgstr "¡Busca cobertura! El enemigo está a punto de hacer gala de sus cohetes."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/06"
msgid ""
"Do not build defences much norther from the main road! This area is where "
"the soviets think we have our defensive lines. I'm sure they will bomb the "
"hell out of it. "
msgstr "¡No formes defensas más al norte de la carretera principal! Los soviéticos creen que hemos instalado líneas defensivas ahí. Estoy seguro de que nos bombardearán con todo. "

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/07"
msgid ""
"As I predicted, they thought our defences were further North... Well, that's "
"one way to clear our line of fire. Brace yourselves, the enemy will soon "
"make their appearance."
msgstr "Como predije, se creían que nuestras defensas se encontraban más al norte... En fin, esa es una forma de despejar nuestra línea de disparo. Resistid, que el enemigo no tardará en aparecer."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/08"
msgid ""
"You have at your disposal our artillery signallers. Their flares will mark "
"the way for Hoepner's 4th army artillery. Use them sparingly."
msgstr "Tienes a tu disposición a los controladores de artillería. Las bengalas que portan marcan el camino de la 4.ª artillería de Hopener. Úsalas con moderación."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/09"
msgid ""
"Aside from air support, we cut off, so expect no reinforcements. Keep some "
"reserves in the rear to plug holes in the defences."
msgstr "Aparte del apoyo aéreo, estamos solos. No esperes refuerzos. Reserva algunas tropas para cubrir bajas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/10"
msgid ""
"I'm sure they did not like our warm welcome. Stay put, the enemy will try to "
"flank us!"
msgstr "Seguro que no les ha gustado nuestra bienvenida. Mantente alerta, ¡el enemigo nos va a intentar flanquear!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/11"
msgid ""
"Excellent work holding the Bolsheviks in check! However, our neighboring "
"unit was caught ill-prepared. Prepare for an attack from the south-west."
msgstr "¡Buen trabajo manteniendo a los bolchevique a raya! Lo malo es que a nuestra unidad vecina la han pillado de improvisto. Prepárate para un ataque procedente del suroeste."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/12"
msgid "The first soviet elements have arrived from the southwest!"
msgstr "¡Han llegado las primeras unidades soviéticas por el suroeste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/13"
msgid "What the hell is that?! That is no ordinary artillery!!"
msgstr "¡¿Qué coño es eso?! ¡¡No es artillería convencional!!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/14"
msgid ""
"Herr Leutnant, take whatever troops are at your disposal and eliminate the "
"threat!"
msgstr "Herr Leutnant, ¡usa tus tropas para acabar con la amenaza!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/15"
msgid ""
"Excellent job! No further assaults have been reported coming our way. Deal "
"with the remaining enemy tanks in the vicinity, see whether we can salvage "
"some of those heavy beasts. They must weigh at least 40 tons!!"
msgstr "¡Muy buen trabajo! Ese era el último asalto. Encárgate de los tanques enemigos que campan en las inmediaciones, quizá podamos utilizar alguno. Son muy, muy pesados, ¡¡40 toneladas mínimo!!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/16"
msgid ""
"Damn, the weather has worsened significantly. Our aviators will not be able "
"to help us in these conditions!"
msgstr "Vaya, el clima ha empeorado mucho. ¡Nuestros aviadores no nos van a poder ayudar como siga así!"

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf109_1"
msgid "Callsign \"Waldkauz\" is diving for the requested target."
msgstr "El distintivo \"Waldkauz\" se aproxima al objetivo solicitado."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf109_2"
msgid "Air support underway!"
msgstr "¡Apoyo aéreo en camino!"

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf109_3"
msgid ""
"Callsign \"Waldkauz\" reports a \"Rotte\" is being dispatched to the target."
msgstr "El distintivo \"Waldkauz\" indica que hay un \"Rotte\" en camino al objetivo."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf110_1"
msgid "Requesting callsign \"Wirsing\" to bombard the designated area."
msgstr "Solicito distintivo \"Wirsing\" para bombardear la zona designada."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf110_2"
msgid "\"Wirsing\" is underway to bomb your coordinates."
msgstr "\"Wirsing\" se dirige a bombardear las coordenadas."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf110_3"
msgid "An element of ZG26 is on its way."
msgstr "Unidad de ZG26 en camino."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf110_4"
msgid "Requesting callsign \"Wirsing\" to strafe the designated area."
msgstr "Solicito distintivo \"Wirsing\" para ametrallar la zona designada."

msgctxt ""
"mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/airstrike_bf110_5"
msgid "\"Wirsing\" is underway to strafe your coordinates."
msgstr "\"Wirsing\" se dirige a ametrallar las coordenadas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/flak1"
msgid ""
"Our planes are reporting enemy Anti-Aircraft Artillery in the area. They are "
"reluctant to continue close air support strikes until the AAA is taken out. "
"Find them and destroy them!"
msgstr "Nuestros aviones afirman que hay artillería antiaérea en la zona. Se niegan a realizar asaltos aéreos de apoyo hasta que eliminemos a la artillería. ¡Búscala y destrúyela!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/n_1"
msgid "Soviet avalanche from the north!"
msgstr "¡Avalancha soviética procedente del norte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/n_2"
msgid "The Bolsheviks are back from the north!"
msgstr "¡Los bolcheviques han vuelto del norte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/nw_1"
msgid "The enemy is pushing us once more from the north-west."
msgstr "El enemigo nos vuelve a atacar por el noroeste."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/nw_2"
msgid "Enemy tanks approaching from the north west!"
msgstr "¡Los alemanes se acercan por el noroeste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/nw_3"
msgid "Soviet armor inbound from the northwest!"
msgstr "¡Hay un avión soviético que viene del noroeste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/sw_1"
msgid "Enemy wide armor formation coming from the southwest!"
msgstr "¡Se aproxima una formación de blindados enemiga por el suroeste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/sw_2"
msgid "Enemy tanks approaching from the north western road!"
msgstr "¡Se aproximan tanques enemigos por la carretera al noroeste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/officer/sw_3"
msgid "South west! Armor following the road!"
msgstr "¡Al suroeste! ¡Blindado en la carretera!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/player/01"
msgid ""
"The Führer had said we'd encircle the Bolsheviks in Moscow by Christmas. I "
"imagine he failed to specify which Christmas that would be.."
msgstr "El Führer pronosticó que en Navidad tendríamos a los bolcheviques rodeados en Moscú. Supongo que se refería a la Navidad de otro año."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/player/02"
msgid "TAKE COVER!!"
msgstr "¡¡A CUBIERTO!!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/player/03"
msgid "Shit! Our commander in chief is dead!"
msgstr "¡Mierda! ¡Ha muerto nuestro comandante al mando!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/player/04"
msgid ""
"The Bolsheviks have entered the premises of the headquarters! They must be "
"driven out immediately, our command is at risk!"
msgstr "¡Los bolcheviques se han adentrado en las premisas de la sede! Tenemos que expulsarlos cuanto antes, ¡el mando está en riesgo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/player/05"
msgid ""
"Soviets in the vicinity of HQ! Our commanding officer and our staff are in "
"danger!"
msgstr "¡Soviéticos en vecindades de la sede! ¡Nuestro oficial y personal están en peligro!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/narrator/player/06"
msgid ""
"Damn it! Soviets close to our headquarters! Our staff must be protected!"
msgstr "¡Mierda! ¡Se aproximan soviéticos a nuestra sede! ¡Hay que proteger al personal!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"The solid stand of the 9th Army along with the heroic contribution of the "
"Luftwaffe caused Konev's forces to fail in their encirclement of army group "
"centre. \n"
"The counterattack of the Soviets stagnated in February. The new frontline "
"layout led to the meat grinder of Rzhev and other battles where, in spite of "
"terrible losses, the soviet sacrifice had secured the capital. Hitler then "
"turned south towards the caucasus and Stalingrad, meaning that Moscow would "
"be securely in Soviet hands and no future attempts to capture it would take "
"place. Operation Typhoon had failed."
msgstr "La resistencia de la 9.ª Armada junto a la contribución heroica de la Luftwaffe provocó que las tropas de Konev fracasaran en su intento por rodear a la milicia. \nEl contrataque de los soviéticos se estancó en febrero. Por otro lado, el diseño del nuevo frente de batalla ocasionó una masacre en Rzhev. Aunque otras batallas en las que hubo también un gran número de pérdidas sirvieron para asegurar la capital. Es por eso que Hitler marchó hacia el sur, en dirección al Cáucaso y Stalingrado, permitiendo así que Moscú permaneciera en manos soviéticas y no hubiera más intentos por capturarla. La Operación Tifón había fracasado."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"Losing this battle means the main body of army group centre will quickly get "
"surrounded and, their supplies dwindling, a catastrophic loss of men and "
"vehicles \n"
"seems at hand. Not only that; we have lost control over the Dnieper "
"crossings once again. This is even worse than going back to square one."
msgstr "La pérdida de esta batalla significa que el cuerpo del Grupo de Ejércitos Centro será rodeado en breves y, por la escasez de víveres, se \navecinan una enorme pérdida militar y de vehículos. Pero no solo eso, además, hemos vuelto a perder el control de los cruces de Dniéper. La situación es peor, si cabe, que al comienzo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/place"
msgid "9th Army,  Army Group Centre."
msgstr "9.ª Armada, Grupo de Ejércitos Centro."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/reinf_110_50"
msgid "Bf-110 SC-50"
msgstr "Bf-110 SC-50"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/reinf_110_500"
msgid "Bf-110 SC-500"
msgstr "Bf-110 SC-500"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/reinf_110_guns"
msgid "Bf-110 Strafing"
msgstr "Bombardeo Bf-110"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/story"
msgid "With Operation Typhoon brought to a standstill, Stavka counterattacks, forcing the Wehrmacht into a defensive stance and pushing them back to positions previously captured in October."
msgstr "Con la Operación Tifón en pausa, Stavka contratacó y obligó a la Wehrmacht a adoptar una postura defensiva retrocediendo a posiciones que habían capturado en octubre."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/task1"
msgid ""
"Do not let the enemy overrun the village. Protect the headquarters at all "
"costs!"
msgstr "No dejes que el enemigo invada la aldea. ¡Protege la sede cueste lo que cueste!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/task2"
msgid "Take out the heavy artillery and neutralise the soviet position."
msgstr "Acaba con la artillería pesada y neutraliza la posición soviética."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/taskopt1"
msgid "Take out the AAA for the air support to resume."
msgstr "Acaba con la artillería antiaérea para que prosiga el apoyo aéreo."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/taskopt2"
msgid "Salvage at least one soviet heavy KV-class tank."
msgstr "Conserva al menos un tanque soviético del grupo KV."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_01_vyazma/timer"
msgid "Defend the headquarters:"
msgstr "Defiende la sede:"
